texts.text: 1.7.4[1] is a minor update to Minecraft (Java Edition) that was released on December 10, 2013.[2] Additions included a new Mojang splash screen, Twitch.tv broadcasting and the chicken jockey. While it was not the last update to 1.7, it was the last one before the snapshots of 1.8 started.
A pre-release for 1.7.4 was released on December 9, 2013.[3][4] 1.7.4 was later re-uploaded.[more information needed] 1.7.4 is the final version released in 2013.

Consists of a baby zombie riding and controlling a chicken.
Because the zombie is riding a chicken, it cannot take fall damage.
As it is a baby zombie, it will not burn up if exposed to daylight.
Extremely rare - every baby zombie spawned has a very small chance of spawning as a chicken jockey.
Baby zombie villager chicken jockeys consist of a baby zombie villager riding a chicken.
Zombie pigmen chicken jockeys can spawn in the Nether.

Microphone can be recorded too.
Twitch chat integration in the game.

Broadcast Settings:
Quality, Framerate, Bandwidth, Send Metadata, Mic Volume, System Volume, Compression, Enable Chat and User Filter (for the twitch chat).

Sheep with the custom name "jeb_" change their color, fading between all 16 wool colors.[7]
Commonly referred to as "rainbow sheep", "disco sheep", or "Jeb sheep".
Color changes are visual effects only; does not affect wool drops.
The sharpness enchantment now affects the "attack damage" attribute.
When dismounting entities, players are no longer moved as far.
If all auto-completable options begin the same, tab will fill up the beginning - Example: /gamerule doM completes to /gamerule doMob.

The logo has been changed so now it's red instead of red-orange, has 2 square corners, and the rounded corners are rounder. The text is now black instead of orange, the font weight is lighter (bold instead of black), and the face appears to be a custom hybrid of Insignia and Code pro.
Mojang splash screen can no longer be changed in resource packs.

Servers now have an icon which is the face of the owner's skin.
Config screen is modified - layout changed.

3 issues fixed
From released versions before 1.7.4
MC-12964 – Server performance issue: Chunk coordinates use a bad hash function.

MC-41623 – "Force Unicode Font" button in languages section of the options doesn't work if GUI Scale is set to "Auto".
MC-41668 – "Old graphics card detected" watermark on title screen is in quotes.

1.7.4 has 8 snapshots, making it have the most snapshots among all minor updates.
1.7.4 is tied with 1.16.2 as the minor update with the most total development versions.
1.7.4 is the only minor update to have more than two snapshots be released in a single week.
"Minecraft 1.7.4 has been released! Get it via the launcher!" – @jeb_ on Twitter, December 10, 2013
"We've pre-released a new version of Minecraft, 1.7.4, to fix some crashes. Full release tomorrow maybe." – @Dinnerbone on Twitter, December 9, 2014
